      h1 Apply for help with fees
      p.large You may not have to pay a court or tribunal fee, or you may get some money off.
  br
  .row
    .small-12.columns
      h3
        img src="../../assets/images/icon-sml-process-home.png" width="36px" height="36px"
        |&nbsp; You're likely to get help
      br
      div.bold You're receiving one of these benefits:
      div Jobseeker's Allowance (JSA)
      div Employment and Support Allowance (ESA)
      div Income Support
      div Universal Credit
      div Pension Credit
      div Scottish Civil Legal Aid
      br
      div.bold You earn less than:
      div £1,085 a month
      div 
        |(this can include benefits, eg working tax credit, child tax credit)
      br
      div.bold You have less than:
      div £3,000 in savings and investments
      br
      br

    .small-12.columns
      h3
        img src="../../assets/images/icon-sml-maybe-eligible.png" width="36px" height="36px"
        |&nbsp; You may still get help
      br
      div.bold You earn more than:
      div £1,085 a month <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/courtfinder/forms/ex160a-eng-2015.11.pdf#page=8" target="_blank"> check the guide</a>
      br
      div.bold You have more than:
      div £3,000 in savings and investments <a href="http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/courtfinder/forms/ex160a-eng-2015.11.pdf#page=5" target="_blank"> check the guide</a>
      br
      hr
      br
    
      h3 What you'll need:
      ul
        li National Insurance number
        li court or tribunal form name or number
        li case, claim or ‘notice to pay’ number (if you have one)
        li most recent bank statement for all current accounts
        li most recent payslip (if you have one)
        li most recent tax return (if you're self employed)
      br
      p Applying takes around 10 minutes. This service is for England and Wales only.
      br

